HEADWORD: Kansas
<hw>Kan"sas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A state of the
central United States, bordering the Mississippi River to the
west.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kansas</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Kansas
<hw>Kan"sas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A tribe of Indians allied to the Winnebagoes
and Osages. They formerly inhabited the region which is now the State of
Kansas, but were removed to the Indian Territory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

